I had no idea that Velious had 3 different factions to work toward.  How does this influence our Guild?  I'm guessing we currently have dragon faction, based on the fact that Gorenaire did not seem inclined to chew us up the other night.  Plus, I imagine our giant faction can't be good after bringing down all their brethren in the Rathe Mountains.  But what about Thurgadin?  Isn't that the dwarves?  Nine?  I realize that this board discusses places too high for us now.  What I want to know is:  should we be concerned with this? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uopusorcharmer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Opus Orcharmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(9/5/01 2:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious Faction</span><hr size=1> OK the answer to this is very simple. I talked to my cousin Rexx in Thurgadin. He said all we need to do is kill giants. They are big ugly and stupid. No one will miss a few giants. Also, killing giants makes everyone happy. Dwarves and Dragons both hate giants. Killing dwarves is simply out of the question. I cant abide by murdering my own relatives to get ahead. It would be like Druids and Rangers killing bears. I am very concerned that Curlington and Tormenter have different ideas. The evil members of the guild may try to help the giants kill dwarves. So keep an eye on them. <br>
<br>
